snippet.title: Real Talk 2020 highlights the important role of CSP networks
snippet.description:
CSPs need to operate high performing, secure and resilient networks. In this Real Talk session hosted by Amber Mac, Nokia's new President and CEO, Pekka Lundmark, opens the virtual event with his view on the post COVID-19 reality for CSPs, and asks what role they might play in the emerging 5G ecosystems. We also hear from Nokia's Tommi Uitto, President of Mobile Networks, as he describes the need to build high performing and resilient networks for the 5G era. And through the eyes of a hacker, Keren Elazari, we look at how 5G and IoT are changing the threat landscape just when the need to feel digitally secure has never been greater. And finally the world's most connected person, Chris Dancy, talks about why he is convinced we are headed towards a world full of wisdom and not division.
For more from #NokiaRealTalk session 1, visit: https://www.nokia.com/networks/csp/real-talk-2020/videos/session-1/
To explore our speakers, visit: https://www.nokia.com/networks/csp/real-talk-2020/videos
